Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • Model
  • public class Model
extends java.util.Observable
    This is model class which contains whole game logic for minesweeper. It's observable and certain functions notify observers by certain messages.
    Author:
    Tomek

    • Method Detail

      • changeMode

        public void changeMode​(int width,
                       int height,
                       int bombs)
        This function is used to change parameters of game such as field size and number of bombs. It will build new board, update model parameters, reset timer, first-click flag and notify observers by "changed field" message.
        Parameters:
        width - - width of field
        height - - height of field
        bombs - - number of bombs in game

      • resetTimerThread

        public void resetTimerThread()
        This function resets timer back to zero and notify observers by message "timer".

      • startTimerThread

        public void startTimerThread()
        This functions sets timerRunning variable to true and calls resetTimerThread() to start timer thread.

      • setTimerThread

        public void setTimerThread()
        This function sets new thread which purpose is to increment timer by one every second. It does it's when game is running (that means it is not won or lost and first move was made). It notifies observers when timer is incremented by message "timer".

      • buildBoard

        public void buildBoard()
        Fills board with blank fields.

      • placeBombs

        public void placeBombs​(int xForbidden,
                       int yForbidden)
        Function places number of bombs specified by model's totalBombs variable. It places them by randomly selecting field without any bomb and which is not forbidden from having bomb.
        Parameters:
        xForbidden - - x position of field which can't have bomb.
        yForbidden - - y position of field which can't have bomb.

      • calcNeighbours

        public void calcNeighbours()
        Calculate how many bombs are on adjacent fields and mark it on that field's neighbors variable. Function checks whether or not it would go out of game board array boundaries.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        This function resets whole game (removes bombs, zeroes timer etc.) and sends observers notifications When notifying observers it sends "bombCounter", "redraw" and "reset" messages. It uses multiple functions to reset each part of board (see resetBoard() and resetTimerThread())

      • resetBoard

        public void resetBoard()
        This function resets game board. It calls reset function for each field on the board.

      • revealZeros

        public void revealZeros​(int x,
                        int y)
        This function is used to reveal all fields with zero neighbors adjacent to the clicked field (including it). It will do it as long as there are adjacent unrevealed zero fields and is within game board bounds. Function can call itself multiple times.
        Parameters:
        x - - x position in array
        y - - y position in array

      • revealTile

        public void revealTile​(int x,
                       int y)
        This function will reveal unrevealed field. If it is first click of the game, function will call functions to place bombs and calculate neighbors. If the revealed field contained bomb, function will set game status as lost. It also checks if the move will end the game (see endGame()). It also notifies observers by message "redraw".
        Parameters:
        x - - x position in array
        y - - y position in array

      • changeState

        public void changeState​(int x,
                        int y)
        This function is called when user wants to flag or remove flag from field. It notifies observers by message "bombCounter" if flag was added or removed and by message "redraw". It also checks for the end of game (see endGame()
        Parameters:
        x - - x position in array
        y - - y position in array

      • endGame

        public void endGame()
        This function checks if the game has ended and if yes in which way. If game status is "lost" then the game is lost and function notifies observers by sending "lost". Otherwise if all fields with bomb have been marked and all other fields were revealed then the game is won and observers are notifies by "won" message.
